 {"id":"bd-devbv","title":"add mounted-path E2E and ioctl-trace coverage for ext4 EXT4_IOC_GETVERSION","description":"Survey finding: `FsOps::get_inode_version` exists in `crates/ffs-core/src/vfs.rs`, `ffs-fuse` dispatches `EXT4_IOC_GETVERSION`, and `crates/ffs-fuse/src/lib.rs` has direct dispatch tests, but `crates/ffs-harness/tests/fuse_e2e.rs` has no mounted-path proof for the ioctl.\n\nScope:\n- Add a mounted-path helper in `fuse_e2e.rs` that issues `EXT4_IOC_GETVERSION` against a real ext4 file over FUSE.\n- Assert the ioctl-trace log records the command when the kernel forwards it, and soft-skip only when the kernel/VFS rejects before userspace dispatch.\n- Verify stable value encoding and buffer-size/errno behavior against the mounted path, not only the unit-dispatch shim.\n- Update `FEATURE_PARITY.md` if operator-visible coverage now exists.\n\nAcceptance:\n- At least one mounted-path `EXT4_IOC_GETVERSION` scenario exists with deterministic assertions.\n- CI artifacts make it clear whether failures are transport-layer skips or FrankenFS regressions.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T03:16:09.486713081Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T15:04:21.391364637Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T15:04:21.389261856Z","close_reason":"done","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ext4","fuse","ioctl","testing"]}
